== Step 3: Untestable Requirements

|===
| Requirement | Why Is It Untestable? | Rewrite to Make It Testable

| MR-01: "The system shall remain operational during supervised usability testing. No unplanned downtime requiring restart shall occur during testing sessions"
| What defines "testing sessions"? How long are they? What counts as "unplanned downtime"? A 2-second network retry? A 30-second Supabase connection loss? If a test session is 8 hours, is any restart a failure?
| "During any 60-minute supervised usability testing session, the system shall experience zero unplanned restarts. Planned maintenance or explicit developer restarts are excluded. Network-related temporary disconnections (under 10 seconds) that auto-recover without user intervention do not count as downtime."

| MR-02: "No participant shall abandon a task due to perceived slowness"
| "Perceived slowness" is entirely subjective. One user's "fast" is another user's "slow." No participant abandoning a task is impossible to guarantee because abandonment depends on user personality, patience, and external distractions.
| "For each usability testing session with 5 participants, 100% of participants shall complete the following tasks without manually canceling or navigating away: (1) add an item in under 60 seconds, (2) view low-stock alerts in under 3 seconds, (3) mark an item as consumed in under 10 seconds. Measured by screen recording timestamps."

| DR-14: "The system shall deduplicate alerts and trigger them primarily on actionable state transitions, so that repeated checks without state change do not generate repeated alerts."
| "Primarily" is not measurable. What percentage of alerts must come from state transitions? 90%? 95%? 99%? Also, what counts as a "repeated check"? Every minute? Every hour? Every AutoCheck run?
| "The system shall generate alerts ONLY on actionable state transitions (NORMAL→LOW_STOCK, IN_STOCK→OUT_OF_STOCK, VALID→EXPIRED). The AutoCheck process running daily shall NOT generate new alerts for any item whose state has not changed since the previous day's AutoCheck. Zero duplicate alerts shall be generated across consecutive daily runs when no state changes occur."

|===

